COMPONENT NAME: LKM File to MSSQL (BULK)
AUTHOR: Oracle
DESCRIPTION - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from a file to a Microsoft SQL Server BULK INSERT sql statement.
OPTIONS DATAFILETYPE: specifies that BULK INSERT performs the copy operation using the specified default. DELETE_TEMPORARY_OBJECTS: allows to delete the temporary objects CODEPAGE: default code page for the Bulk Insert
LIMITATIONS - Works only with delimited fields - When possible avoid performing data transformations. - the file must be accessible from the SQL Server machine.

Specifies that BULK INSERT performs the copy operation using the specified default.
DATAFILETYPE : char | native | widechar | widenative
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

Default code page for the Bulk Insert
CODEPAGE : ACP | OEM | RAW | code_page

BULK INSERT <%=odiRef.getObjectName("T"+odiRef.getTableName("COLL_SHORT_NAME"),"W")%> FROM '<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[SCHEMA]/[RES_NAME]", "", "")%>' WITH ( CODEPAGE = '<%=odiRef.getOption("CODEPAGE")%>' , DATAFILETYPE = '<%=odiRef.getOption("DATAFILETYPE")%>' , FIELDTERMINATOR ='<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_SEP_FIELD]", "", "")%>' , FIRSTROW =<% first_row = new Integer(odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_FIRST_ROW]", "", "")).intValue(); out.print(first_row+1);%> , TABLOCK )
DEMO.LKM File to MSSQL (BULK).Drop work view
DEMO.LKM File to MSSQL (BULK).Drop work table
